Spiaggia Libera #10

Artist: Malaury Buis  
Medium: Fuji Superia 200 - Canon AT1  
Edition: 1/1  
Location: Pozzuoli, Italy

About The Project:  

A Collection entirely shot on expired film, about a one-of-a-kind beach in the gulf of Naples, Italy.  
This beach used to be the greatest port in Italy more than 2500 years ago (512 BC). Nowadays itâ€™s a block of concrete where the locals are burning their skins all day during the summer. With a direct view of Capri Island, a calm and warm Mediterranean Sea this place seems peaceful and out of time.
